## SECTION 6 — DATABASE RULES (MEMORIZE THIS)

```typescript
// Single connection — ALWAYS import from here
import { db } from '@/lib/db';

// Relational queries for reads
await db.query.orders.findFirst({ with: { items: true } });

// Core queries for mutations
await db.insert(orders).values(newOrder);
await db.update(orders).set({ status: 'paid' }).where(eq(orders.id, id));

// TRANSACTIONS for these operations (mandatory):
// 1. Payment settlement: status → paid + stock deduction + points award
// 2. Order cancellation: status → cancelled + coupon reversal
// 3. Points redemption: deduct balance + create history record

// Stock deduction — ALWAYS atomic
await tx.update(productVariants).set({
  stock: sql`GREATEST(stock - ${qty}, 0)`,
}).where(and(eq(productVariants.id, variantId), gte(productVariants.stock, qty)));
// Check affected rows — if 0, abort transaction (insufficient stock)

// Prices — ALWAYS integer IDR, never float
// Timestamps — ALWAYS UTC in DB, WIB for display
// Soft delete — products and users use deleted_at column
```

