## SECTION 10 — CRITICAL FLOWS (READ CAREFULLY)

### Checkout Flow
```
1. Customer reviews cart
2. Enters identity (name, email, phone) — guest or logged-in
3. Selects delivery method: Delivery or Pickup
4. If Delivery:
   a. Selects or enters address (province → city → details)
   b. GET /api/checkout/shipping-rates (RajaOngkir, cold-chain only)
   c. Selects courier from returned options
5. Enters coupon code (optional) → POST /api/checkout/validate-coupon
6. Redeems points (optional, max 50% of subtotal, logged-in only)
7. Reviews full order summary
8. Submits → POST /api/checkout/initiate:
   a. Re-fetch all prices from DB (never trust client)
   b. Re-check stock for all variants
   c. Validate coupon again server-side
   d. Calculate points discount
   e. Create order record (status: pending_payment)
   f. Create order_items with SNAPSHOTS of product data
   g. Create Midtrans transaction → get snap_token
   h. Save snap_token + payment_expires_at to order
   i. Return { orderId, orderNumber, snapToken }
9. Client opens Midtrans Snap popup with snapToken
10. Customer pays
11. Midtrans calls POST /api/webhooks/midtrans:
    a. Verify signature FIRST
    b. Check idempotency (already paid?)
    c. If settlement: run DB transaction:
       - Update order status → paid
       - Deduct stock (atomic, check for 0)
       - Increment coupon.used_count
       - Award loyalty points to user (if not guest)
       - Set order.paid_at = now
    d. Return 200 OK immediately
    e. Send confirmation email async (non-blocking)
12. Customer sees /orders/success/[orderNumber]
```

### Payment Retry Flow
```
- Payment expires after 15 minutes
- Customer can retry up to 3 times
- Each retry: new Midtrans order_id = DDK-YYYYMMDD-XXXX-retry-N
- Old snap_token discarded, new one generated
- Order status stays pending_payment through retries
```

### Stock Deduction (Atomic Pattern)
```typescript
const result = await tx
  .update(productVariants)
  .set({ stock: sql`GREATEST(stock - ${qty}, 0)` })
  .where(and(
    eq(productVariants.id, variantId),
    gte(productVariants.stock, qty)
  ))
  .returning({ newStock: productVariants.stock });

if (result.length === 0) {
  throw new StockError(variantId); // triggers transaction rollback
}
```

### Coupon Validation Rules (ALL must pass)
```
1. Coupon exists in DB
2. is_active = true
3. expires_at IS NULL OR expires_at > now
4. starts_at IS NULL OR starts_at <= now
5. max_uses IS NULL OR used_count < max_uses
6. subtotal >= min_order_amount
7. If max_uses_per_user: user usage count < max_uses_per_user
8. If applicable_product_ids: at least one cart item matches
9. If applicable_category_ids: at least one cart item matches
```

### Points System Rules
```
Earn:   1 point per Rp 1.000 of subtotal (not shipping, not discount)
        B2B users: 2x multiplier
        Only after payment settlement, never before
        Only for logged-in users (not guest)
        Expires: 365 days from earn date

Redeem: 100 points minimum
        Max 50% of order subtotal
        1 point = Rp 1 discount
        FIFO — oldest non-expired points used first
        Can combine with coupon

Expire: Cron job checks daily for points expiring in 30 days → send email
        On expiry date: create 'expire' record, reduce points_balance
```

